attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, ARM, version 1 (ARM), statically linked, stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a Mirai-variant botnet designed for ARM-based IoT devices. It features classic malicious behaviors including automated Telnet brute-forcing using an extensive embedded list of default credentials (found in function sub_13e08, e.g., 'root/Pon521', 'admin/admin123'). The sample performs process discovery by scanning /proc to identify and terminate competing malware. It also utilizes system utilities like busybox for remote payload acquisition (via wget, tftp, ftpget) and execution. The presence of specific command templates like '/.ffaaxx telnet.echo' and HTTP User-Agent 'Wget' are strong indicators of its botnet functionality.
